      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dataframe-construction-from-backend-sources/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The Spectra package natively supports import of MS data from mzML, mzXML and netCDF files and through its add-on packages MsBackendMgf, MsBackendMsp and MsBackendMassbank from files in MGF, MSP or MassBank format. It is thus possible to use for example results from MS-DIAL or MZmine as input for matchSpectra by importing them with qry <- Spectra('mzmine_result.mgf', source = MsBackendMgf()). Alternatively, query MS2 spectra can also be directly extracted from a xcms result objects with qry <- featureSpectra(xdata, return.type = 'Spectra').",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses Spectra package and MsBackend infrastructure for handling spectra data and multiple backend implementations (MsBackendMgf, MsBackendMsp, MsBackendMassbank), but does not explicitly describe the spectraData() method, fillCoreSpectraVariables() function, or the specific pattern of filling missing core variables with NA. The paper confirms the existence of MsBackend framework and multiple backend implementations but does not detail the DataFrame construction mechanism claimed in the research question.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo12020173",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dataframe-construction-from-backend-sources",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Construct a DataFrame object containing complete spectra variables by implementing a spectraData() method that retrieves user-supplied variables from a backend storage slot and fills missing core spectra variables with NA values.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:11:11.386813+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dataframe-construction-from-backend-sources/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The basic infrastructure for spectra similarity calculations is provided by the Spectra package with the compareSpectra() function. Spectra similarity calculations are performed as a two-step approach: first, peaks from the query and target spectrum are mapped to each other based on their m/z values and a given error (absolute or in ppm), and then a similarity score is calculated based on these matched peaks.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Spectra package exists and provides infrastructure for MS data handling and multiple backend implementations (MsBackendMgf, MsBackendMsp, MsBackendMassbank are explicitly mentioned). However, the paper does not explicitly mention the fillCoreSpectraVariables() utility function or detail the spectraData() method implementation pattern described in the card.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo12020173",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dataframe-construction-from-backend-sources",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Spectra - Framework providing the MsBackend virtual class, fillCoreSpectraVariables() utility function, and Spectra object infrastructure",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:11:11.386813+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
