    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/peak-data-extraction-and-formatting/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The Spectra package natively supports import of MS data from mzML, mzXML and netCDF files and through its add-on packages MsBackendMgf, MsBackendMsp and MsBackendMassbank from files in MGF, MSP or MassBank format. It is thus possible to use for example results from MS-DIAL or MZmine as input for matchSpectra by importing them with qry <- Spectra('mzmine_result.mgf', source = MsBackendMgf()). Alternatively, query MS2 spectra can also be directly extracted from a xcms result objects with qry <- featureSpectra(xdata, return.type = 'Spectra').",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses Spectra package and MsBackend classes but does not explicitly detail peak data extraction methods (peaksData(), intensity(), mz()) or NumericList/matrix formatting. The paper focuses on high-level annotation workflows rather than backend implementation details. The card's claim about 'implementing standardized accessor methods' and 'NumericList or matrix structures' is not directly addressed in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo12020173",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
