      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/r-object-size-measurement-and-benchmarking/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The Spectra package natively supports import of MS data from mzML, mzXML and netCDF files and through its add-on packages MsBackendMgf, MsBackendMsp and MsBackendMassbank from files in MGF, MSP or MassBank format [17]. It is thus possible to use for example results from MS-DIAL or MZmine as input for matchSpectra by importing them with qry <- Spectra('mzmine_result.mgf', source = MsBackendMgf()). Alternatively, query MS2 spectra can also be directly extracted from a xcms result objects with qry <- featureSpectra(xdata, return.type = 'Spectra'). As target parameter (variable db in the example above), either a CompDb database or a Spectra object with data imported from MSP or MGF files can be used.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms Spectra package exists and provides spectraData() method and backend framework (MsBackendMgf, MsBackendMsp, MsBackendMassbank), but does NOT discuss MsBackendTest or memory/latency tradeoffs. The card's claim about using these tools for benchmarking memory\u2013speed tradeoffs is not supported by the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo12020173",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "r-object-size-measurement-and-benchmarking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Spectra package provides S4 backend framework (MsBackendTest, spectraData() method) used to implement and test memory/latency tradeoffs in spectra data storage",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:13:23.297496+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/r-object-size-measurement-and-benchmarking/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Passages insufficient to judge. The paper does not mention S4Vectors or DataFrame class in the provided excerpts. While spectraData() is mentioned, the return type and its relationship to S4Vectors is not discussed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-3390-metabo12020173",
